      "status": "new",
      "description": "<h2>2026 Warsaw MI Data – Web Scraping Internship</h2>\n<h3>A career with Point72’s Market Intelligence team</h3>\n<p>On our proprietary research team—<strong>Market Intelligence (MI)</strong>—you’ll partner with our investment professionals and&nbsp;Compliance&nbsp;team to work with alternative data to uncover insights about companies, industries, and the broader economy through deep fundamental research and the application of data science and engineering techniques. You’ll work alongside a talented team with diverse skills, backgrounds, and perspectives. Our sector data analysts, data scientists, data managers, and engineers work together to build compliant research products that are incorporated into the research process of our investment professionals. We look for bright, motivated, and collaborative people to join our team and grow with us—a majority of the leaders in our group were promoted from within.</p>\n<h3>About the Market Intelligence internship</h3>\n<p>As a Data Engineer Intern focused on web scraping, you will gain exposure to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Creating web‑scraping pipelines based on customer requests</li>\n<li>Extracting and ingesting data from websites using Compliance‑approved web crawling tools</li>\n<li>Developing tools, services, and workflows to enhance the speed, efficiency, and stability of scrape development</li>\n<li>Testing data and scrapes to ensure accuracy, quality, and compliance</li>\n<li>Identifying and resolving scraping issues and breakages, as well as scaling scrapes as needed</li>\n<li>Partnering with&nbsp;Compliance&nbsp;to ensure scraping activities align with firm standards</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Summer internship program at Point72</h3>\n<p>In addition to the learning and development you’ll receive in your day‑to‑day role with your team, as part of our summer internship program you will:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Work alongside your fellow interns and be mentored by experienced professionals</li>\n<li>Meet your peers through designated intern programming, volunteer opportunities, and social events</li>\n<li>Attend sessions with senior leaders discussing their expertise and career paths</li>\n<li>Get hands‑on access to best‑in‑class tools and resources</li>\n<li>Gain exposure to groups and functions with unique responsibilities and perspectives on our industry</li>\n<li>Develop technical, writing, and presentation skills</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>What’s required</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>A bachelor’s degree (or expected completion in 2026) in computer science, engineering, or other quantitative disciplines</li>\n<li>Experience or demonstrated interest in web scraping</li>\n<li>Solid understanding of computer science fundamentals (data structures, algorithms, etc.)</li>\n<li>Strong experience in Python development</li>\n<li>Interest in working with data, big data problems, and cloud‑based technologies</li>\n<li>Strong written and verbal communication skills in English</li>\n<li>Commitment to the highest ethical standards</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>About Point72</h3>\n<p><strong>Point72</strong>&nbsp;is a leading global alternative investment firm led by Steven A. Cohen. Building on more than 30 years of investing experience, Point72 seeks to deliver superior returns for its investors through fundamental and systematic investing strategies across asset classes and geographies. We aim to attract and retain the industry’s brightest talent by cultivating an investor‑led culture and committing to our people’s long‑term growth. For more information, visit&nbsp;<a class=\"text-[color:var(--primary-accent-text)]\" href=\"https://point72.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://point72.com/</a>.</p>\n<p>Our Warsaw office gives us access to world‑class talent with a reputation for excellence and innovation. We’re looking to build an office of subject‑matter experts whose fresh perspectives will help evolve our infrastructure and advance the capabilities of our teams. Learn more at Warsaw Office – Point72.</p>",
